Reasoning: The paper discusses the error analysis and optimization of Sigma-Delta modulation, which is a common method for analog-to-digital conversion of bandlimited signals. This topic falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of orthogonal polynomials suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA), while the optimization problem and the use of filters suggest a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and systems and control (cs.SI).
